One person has been reported killed in an attack by thugs on the Soka residence of Yoruba Nation agitator, Sunday 'Igboho' Adeyemo, in Ibadan, Oyo State. This was made known by a media aide to the agitator, Olayomi Koiki, in a chat with SaharaReporters on Saturday. Sunday Igboho According to him, several of the agitator's supporters, who were in the house during the attack, sustained injuries. This was also confirmed in a video he shared with SaharaReporters. The thugs reportedly stormed Igboho’s house and fired shots, leading to the death of one of Igboho's supporters. A voice in the video seen by SaharaReporters said, “Can you see this? This is Oloye Sunday Igboho's house and these are his men that have been attacked without doing anything wrong. "These are the people that got injured, can you see it? They are currently being treated, one of them is dead. The thugs came to attack Sunday Igboho's house. Can you see?”